==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stride
<hw>Stride</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos>
<conjf>Strode</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> (<mark>Obs</mark>.
<conjf>Strid</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>); <pos>p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Stridden</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> (<mark>Obs.</mark>
<conjf>Strid</conjf>); <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Striding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>str⟦imac⟧dan</ets> to
stride, to strive; akin to LG. <ets>striden</ets>, OFries.
<ets>str⟦imac⟧da</ets> to strive, D. <ets>strijden</ets> to strive, to
contend, G. <ets>streiten</ets>, OHG. <ets>str⟦imac⟧tan</ets>; of
uncertain origin. Cf. <er>Straddle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To walk
with long steps, especially in a measured or pompous manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mars in the middle of the shining shield⟦br⟧
Is graved, and <qex>strides</qex> along the liquid field.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To stand with the legs wide apart; to
straddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stride</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stride
<hw>Stride</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pass over at a
step; to step over.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A debtor that not dares to
<xex>stride</xex> a limit.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To straddle; to bestride.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I mean to <qex>stride</qex> your steed.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stride</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Stride
<hw>Stride</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of striding; a long step;
the space measured by a long step; <as>as, a masculine
<ex>stride</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God never meant that man should scale the heavens⟦br⟧
By <qex>strides</qex> of human wisdom.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strident</ent>⟦br⟧
